article_title: ObamaCare May Be Growing The Number Of Unpaid Medical Bills

article_metadata.description: The rising amount of uncollected co-pays and deductibles may be an early sign of consumer stress as the economy weakens. But more likely, it also reflects changes in the healthcare market that are saddling consumers with a much bigger share of their medical costs. For this, ObamaCare is playing a big role.
article_metadata.author: Scott Gottlieb
